hands_on_practices.solution:
We label the three points on the period-3 orbit by $p_0, p_1, p_2$ with $s_0=1, s_1=0, s_2=1$. Their $x$-coordinates satisfy

$$
\begin{aligned}
x_1 &= f_x^{(1)}(x_0) = \frac{x_0-(1-\lambda)}{\lambda},\\
x_2 &= f_x^{(0)}(x_1) = \frac{x_1}{\lambda}
      = \frac{x_0-(1-\lambda)}{\lambda^2},\\
x_3 &= f_x^{(1)}(x_2)
      = \frac{x_2-(1-\lambda)}{\lambda}
      = \frac{\displaystyle x_0-(1-\lambda)-(1-\lambda)\lambda^2}{\lambda^3}.
\end{aligned}
$$

Periodicity $x_3=x_0$ gives

$$
x_0
=\frac{x_0-(1-\lambda)(1+\lambda^2)}{\lambda^3}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
x_0(1-\lambda^3)=(1-\lambda)(1+\lambda^2)
\;\Longrightarrow\;
x_0=\frac{(1-\lambda)(1+\lambda^2)}{1-\lambda^3}
=\frac{1+\lambda^2}{1+\lambda+\lambda^2}.
$$
